==Reception==

[[Bryan Caplan]], blogging at [[EconLog]], called Scott Alexander a "a fascinating new thinker to read – someone who makes me say, 'Tell me everything{{'"}} and elaborated that "he's better than me on several dimensions I deeply value".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://econlog.econlib.org/archives/2014/10/read_scott_alex.html |title=Read Scott Alexander |publisher= Library of Economics and Liberty |website=[[EconLog]] |accessdate=February 11, 2017 |first=Bryan |last=Caplan |date=October 28, 2014}}</ref>

SSC has been linked from [[Marginal Revolution (blog)|Marginal Revolution]] by [[Tyler Cowen]], who called the post "very excellent".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/category/medicine |title=Medicine Archives - Marginal REVOLUTION |publisher=Marginal REVOLUTION |accessdate=February 11, 2017}}</ref>

[[Steve Hsu]] has called SSC posts "excellent".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://infoproc.blogspot.com/2015/02/slate-star-codex-on-ability-effort-and.html |title=Slate Star Codex on ability, effort, and achievement |accessdate=February 11, 2017}}</ref>

